				\begin{document}$$100\mathrm{ \mu m}$$\end{document}100μm laser beam diameter was used for channel fabrication. We got the best engraving by adjusting the engraving speed to 25 mm/s (10%) laser head translation speed and laser beam power to 5-Watt (6%) laser beam power to get less roughness at the lowest available dimensions. The channel profile is a Gaussian shape, as shown in Fig. 1b25.Figure 1
PMMA and PDMS microchannels. (a) Chip schematic drawing. (b) Channel profile. (c) Picture of the PMMA microchannel used in the present study. (d) PDMS microchannel used in the present study.

